<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 10. Stem anatomy of Diplachne gigantea. Upper: Stellate aerenchyma (SA) that occupies much of the central portion of the culm (voucher: Smith 4126 [MO]). Lower: Outer portion of stem showing air canals (AC), chlorenchymatous tissue (CT), vascular bundles (VB), and sclerenchyma bands (SB) surrounding the air canals (voucher: Simon & Williamson 2025 [BM])." , "Figure 9. A-K Diplachne gigantea Launert A habit B inflorescence C ligule D spikelet E lower glume F upper glume G lemma H palea and lodicules I ovary and stigmas J stamen K caryopsis, dorsal view (left) and lateral view (right). Drawings from McCallum Webster A 305 (K), from Zambia." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/181283" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/181282" .

